    "ideation": "The banjo sequence captures the frenetic energy and rhythmic 'twang' of bluegrass. The performance personifies the instrument's percussive nature. The eyes act as the resonator and skin, bouncing with high-speed focus and rhythmic snapping (gaze_y). The mouth represents the vibrating strings: starting as a tight, high-frequency line, it pluck-and-decays repeatedly. I've used rapid scale changes to simulate the physical vibration of a strum. Color shifts from wood-grain brown to a bright metallic brass to mimic the sound of fingerpicks hitting the strings.",
